Welcome to the=C2=A0746=C2=A0newly Not Boring people=C2=A0who have joined u=
s since last Tuesday! If you haven=E2=80=99t subscribed, join=C2=A0184,867 =
smart, curious folks by subscribing here:=20
Today=E2=80=99s Not Boring is brought to you by=E2=80=A6 Wander [ https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/62f0053a-3fa1-488d-ba3f-12f134e69d33?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Last week, I wrote about Wander [ https://substack.com/redirect/2754c8d4-2a=
80-4983-b6bc-c7d512b2c4c0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. It=E2=80=99s already one of our most popular deep dive=
s ever. Here=E2=80=99s a quick refresher:
Wander [ https://substack.com/redirect/5ddd0d69-6025-45e8-8eb8-64e3fd89359d=
?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is a =
network of smart vacation homes that come with inspiring views, modern work=
stations, restful beds, hotel-grade cleaning and 24/7 concierge service =E2=
=80=93=E2=80=93 combining the quality of a luxury hotel with the space and =
comfort of a vacation home, only better. Don=E2=80=99t take my word for it.=
 Use promo code notboring for $250 off your next trip. (Expires Thursday at=
 11:59pm ET). Explore now. [ https://substack.com/redirect/5ddd0d69-6025-45=
e8-8eb8-64e3fd89359d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa=
8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
But that=E2=80=99s only part of the story. Wander recently launched Atlas [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/4be983d9-5e48-4d36-878c-b29086e7780a?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=93=E2=
=80=93 a first-of-its-kind vacation rental REIT that gives you the chance t=
o own a piece of their magical portfolio of homes. With Atlas, accredited i=
nvestors have the opportunity to earn income and diversify their portfolio =
without the headache and hassle of buying a property, renting it out, or ma=
intaining it.
Plus, right now new Atlas investors may get the chance to invest in Wander=
=E2=80=99s next round of funding. You can learn more on their website:
Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Tuesday! Let=E2=80=99s have a little fun today, shall we?=C2=A0
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.
Startup Prophecies
I have a few core beliefs that animate Not Boring:=C2=A0
Startups are key to solving really big challenges.=C2=A0
More people should be able to invest in, and support, startups.=C2=A0=C2=A0
We need more optimistic stories about technology.=C2=A0
I also have a few less-core-but-relevant-here beliefs, which I=E2=80=99ve w=
ritten about:=C2=A0
Business is the New Sports [ https://substack.com/redirect/6465ce49-b9f7-47=
d7-8d96-47dc99fd2045?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa=
8-6m8ExkRNpU ].
Bottoms-up narratives are a powerful way to build worlds. (Story Time [ htt=
ps://substack.com/redirect/e50ee1e2-d39a-4a99-a689-40917d3d6157?j=3DeyJ1Ijo=
iOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ])
In Story Time, I wrote that =E2=80=9CIn a world of abundance, attention is =
the scarcest resource, and people=E2=80=99s attention is hard to earn.=E2=
=80=9D I suggested that startups should shift from top-down storytelling to=
 bottoms-up narrative building, in partnership with their fans and communit=
ies, and that they could take lessons from NFT projects, which create world=
s and then largely turn narrative-building over to the people who own the N=
FTs.=C2=A0
The connection between NFTs and startups in Story Time was loose, just a so=
urce of inspiration for the progressive decentralization of narrative. I wa=
sn=E2=80=99t suggesting that startups should actually create NFTs or encour=
age their fans to do the same.=C2=A0
Then, in October, I read Jacob Horne=E2=80=99s Prophecy Markets [ https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/2a8a63f6-67b3-47f2-ae6a-e230f434e7da?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], and my brain blew up. =
Horne proposed a structure for positive sum prediction markets in which any=
one can make a prediction, mint the prediction as an NFT, and let it trade =
freely. If a bold prediction paired with beautiful art comes true, might th=
at NFT be worth more than it was when it was created? What other benefits c=
ome from giving people shared ownership in the prediction? Horne asks:
Even more interestingly, what does it mean when predictions become positive=
 sum with that level of granularity? Do more people start working together =
to make something a reality? Or stop something from happening? Who knows.
In the spirit of cc0 [ https://substack.com/redirect/b64fba99-f1e3-4282-8bd=
b-40672aa51479?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU ], I=E2=80=99ve been remixing this idea in my head ever since I read=
 the piece four months ago, and can=E2=80=99t stop thinking about how beaut=
ifully it applies to startups.
Swirl all of that together, and here=E2=80=99s the idea: Startup Prophecy M=
arkets.=C2=A0
Startup Prophecy Markets let anyone timestamp predictions about the startup=
s they believe in most by creating art, videos, stories, analysis, and more=
 about the companies=E2=80=99 futures and minting them. Theoretically, if t=
he predictions are bold enough, the content is good enough, and the startup=
s they=E2=80=99re attached to are ambitious enough, those NFTs might be wor=
th more in the future than they are today. A quick scan of eBay reveals a b=
ooming market for early memorabilia from today=E2=80=99s great tech compani=
es.=C2=A0
Even more interestingly, what does it mean to create a rich positive sum ec=
osystem around startups? Do more people start working together to help them=
 succeed? Do NFTs associated with startups tackling the most important prob=
lems become more than those associated with startups that merely become val=
uable? Does it encourage founders to make bolder bets, and provide them wit=
h an army of supporters when they do?
That=E2=80=99s what we=E2=80=99ll explore today. To start, let=E2=80=99s di=
ve into the details of Prophecy Markets.
Prophecy Markets
Prophecy Markets. [ https://substack.com/redirect/2a8a63f6-67b3-47f2-ae6a-e=
230f434e7da?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU ] brainwormed me like nothing I=E2=80=99ve read in a while.=C2=A0
The core idea in Horne=E2=80=99s October essay is that it might be possible=
 to create positive sum prediction markets by using NFTs to capture =E2=80=
=9Cequity in a moment.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
Traditional prediction markets are zero sum. A prediction market ends in a =
binary outcome - $0 or $1. Right now on Kalshi [ https://substack.com/redir=
ect/a7d3c4b9-f7f8-4ab7-8eb6-ed86c567e52a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_=
ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], you can go long Everything Everywhere A=
ll at Once winning Best Picture at the 2023 Oscars for $0.70. If it wins, y=
ou get back $1. If it loses, you get nothing.=C2=A0
Equities, on the other hand, are positive sum. You don=E2=80=99t need someo=
ne to take the other side to invest in a startup, for example, and the upsi=
de is uncapped.=C2=A0
Sequoia made $3 billion from its $60 million investment in WhatsApp. Accel=
=E2=80=99s 15% Series A stake in Thefacebook was worth roughly $9 billion w=
hen Facebook IPO=E2=80=99d in 2012. Masa Son=E2=80=99s $20 million investme=
nt in Alibaba was worth an eye-popping $60 billion when the Chinese ecommer=
ce giant went public in 2014.=C2=A0
No one lost money when those companies succeeded (although the outcomes mus=
t have been painful for investors who passed), but early believers were rew=
arded enormously. Of course, many venture investments go to $0; the differe=
nce is that they=E2=80=99re not capped when they succeed.=C2=A0
What would it look like to design prediction markets that behave more like =
equities?=C2=A0
Horne proposes minting predictions as NFTs. But he starts the thought exerc=
ise crypto-free.
He gives an example of an artist who predicts that an alien spacecraft will=
 visit humanity for the first time on December 1, 2025 by hovering over the=
 Eiffel Tower. The artist paints 10 pictures of the spacecraft floating abo=
ve the Eiffel Tower, asks a journalist to timestamp in print, sells two cop=
ies for $100 each (one to the journalist and one to an amused reader), and =
locks the rest in storage.
Lo and behold, against all odds, on December 1, 2025, there it is: an alien=
 spacecraft hovering over the Eiffel Tower. What would those original paint=
ings be worth?=C2=A0
Are these paintings worth $100? Perhaps $10,000 each? Maybe more? It=E2=80=
=99s hard to imagine a case where they are the same price or cheaper=E2=80=
=94but admittedly it is hard to say how much they would be worth. If they a=
re selling for more, then the artist has effectively created an object that=
 represents ownership over that prediction, and has been able to capture va=
lue as a result without having to find a counterparty. They have created eq=
uity in a moment=E2=80=94aka positive sum prediction market.
So now let's imagine instead of the artist painting physical works, they si=
mply minted it as an NFT=E2=80=94
=E2=80=9CNFTs?!=E2=80=9D you might be asking yourself. =E2=80=9CAren=E2=80=
=99t those dead? JPow gets a little dovish and we=E2=80=99re back to talkin=
g about NFTs?=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
Horne anticipates your pushback (emphasis mine):=C2=A0
=E2=80=94not because we like NFTs (we may or may not), but because we get a=
ll of the functionality that the artist had at lower cost and effort. By mi=
nting as an NFT this means that they get the time stamping functionality ou=
t of the box (impossible to fake), visible to the entire public (by nature =
of being on the blockchain) and also happens to be tradable before and afte=
r the fact.
The Official Not Boring Take=E2=84=A2=EF=B8=8F on NFTs has always been that=
 they=E2=80=99re an incredibly useful primitive that will get more useful w=
ith time. As I wrote in Web3 Use Cases: Today [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/b72a022f-3dc6-45ce-bcb4-40795a70eb97?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]:
Simply, NFTs give physical properties to digital items, making them unique,=
 ownable, and tradeable, in addition to digital properties like programmabi=
lity and composability. Over time, NFTs will represent things that are more=
 useful than the things they represent today, but even today, the collectib=
les use case is a real one.
Even now, the NFT market is coming back to life, seen more clearly in the n=
umber of trades than in the dollar volume:
And it=E2=80=99s evolving. Checks [ https://substack.com/redirect/78a623ce-=
9879-4361-b9b9-f653993fc16b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXe=
pKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] by Jack Butcher [ https://substack.com/redirect/e82ca=
24a-a69d-4492-b3ee-ffac204f5f5f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjm=
lXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is one of the most fun projects I=E2=80=99ve seen=
 in a while. Visible [ https://substack.com/redirect/c68bc73a-dc8b-4df3-928=
8-8aa842e8020f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU ] is using NFTs as digital titles to homes. DIMO [ https://substack.=
com/redirect/5446e3fb-d154-4d04-b603-c9cfc6914206?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb=
8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is using NFTs to store your car=
=E2=80=99s data. And Prophecy Markets feels like a truly native and novel s=
tructure that could only exist in its fullness with NFTs.=C2=A0
Prophecy Markets is one of those =E2=80=9Cstart out looking like a toy [ ht=
tps://substack.com/redirect/f6866cfb-b6fd-401b-a59d-0fdd130f0c3c?j=3DeyJ1Ij=
oiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]=E2=80=9D ideas t=
hat could become really powerful. It takes advantage of all of the things t=
hat NFTs are uniquely good at to create a new market structure designed for=
 a world of abundance. After I read it, I became more convinced that NFTs a=
re going to become an increasingly important piece of our digital lives.=C2=
=A0
Because the real value isn=E2=80=99t in the price of the predictions, but i=
n the rich worlds that can develop around them.=C2=A0
What would happen to the startup ecosystem if we introduced Startup Prophec=
ies?=C2=A0
Startup Prophecies
Startup Prophecies are a derivative of Prophecy Markets that let anyone per=
missionlessly create and mint predictions, art, analysis, code, videos, sto=
ries, and more around startups. These Startup Prophecy NFTs can be traded, =
creating a 3D market on top of the more linear venture funding market. =C2=
=A0
The thing that excites me about this idea is that, unlike alien landings, p=
eople can actually influence startup outcomes. They can tell stories, sprea=
d awareness, call their Senators, make customer introductions, and build a =
richer world around the missions they believe in. This is decentralized sto=
rytelling or web3 media that is company-centric but not company-directed:
Here=E2=80=99s how it works, at its most basic:=C2=A0
Create. Anyone can create predictions, art, stories, music, code, spreadshe=
ets, whatever related to a startup that they think will be more valuable or=
 important in the future than it is today.=C2=A0
Mint. They can mint those items as NFTs, and give or sell editions to other=
 people who believe that those startups will be more valuable or important =
in the future than they are today, or to those who just want to support the=
 company=E2=80=99s mission.=C2=A0
Trade. Between now and the prediction, there=E2=80=99s a liquid market for =
the NFTs that roughly tracks sentiment around those companies.=C2=A0
Appreciate. If those startups end up being more valuable or important than =
they are today, maybe those NFTs will be more valuable than they are today.=
=C2=A0
I don=E2=80=99t think that the value of the assets will tightly track the v=
alue of companies, and I don=E2=80=99t think that there will be a market fo=
r every company=E2=80=99s NFTs. Companies can become valuable without becom=
ing important, and my guess is that NFTs associated with the ones that beco=
me important will be worth more than those for the ones that simply become =
valuable. Which, in my opinion, is a feature.=C2=A0
Startup Prophecy NFTs are not shares in the company. They=E2=80=99re loosel=
y connected not by legal documents, but by memes. People will naturally be =
more attracted to the stories attached to companies that can take us to Mar=
s, cure cancer, or birth AGI =E2=80=93 Hard Startups that do new and import=
ant things =E2=80=93 than they are to those about yet another CRM or an ite=
rative workflow product. Startup Prophecies will reward Good Quests [ https=
://substack.com/redirect/56ef1384-d220-4b0f-ad87-8f26da1554e8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiO=
XAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
A few hypothetical historical examples might paint the picture.=C2=A0
Imagine that a digital artist created an image of a SpaceX rocketship landi=
ng on Mars in 2040 way back in 2003, when the company was founded, minted t=
en of them, and sold them for $100. It=E2=80=99s hard to imagine those woul=
dn=E2=80=99t be worth more than $100 today, and harder to imagine they woul=
dn=E2=80=99t be much more valuable if SpaceX actually lands on Mars in 2040=
=2E=C2=A0
Imagine that way back in 1976, Apple minted 100 editions of its original lo=
go and gave them to its first 100 customers. Those would be worth something=
 today.=C2=A0
Imagine that a sci-fi writer wrote an optimistic short story about a world =
in which OpenAI figures out AGI when the company launched in 2015, minted i=
t, and sold 1,000 copies at a market clearing price. The proceeds might hav=
e allowed her to keep writing full-time. NFTs of the short stories would li=
kely have increased in value with each breakthrough the company made over t=
he past few years, and exploded with the launch of ChatGPT. They=E2=80=99d =
probably be worth even more if OpenAI ultimately achieves its mission.=C2=
=A0
Forget the NFT piece for a second. As you read this, there are multiple fir=
st edition Isaac Asimov books for auction on eBay [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/c99413ad-cbeb-4a3e-bb73-91b77dbbfcf0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] at over $1,000, with a signed First E=
dition Trilogy as high as $32,000.=C2=A0
There are dozens of old school Apple t-shirts [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/241b2b33-5158-43dd-870a-5171df7df3b4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] on offer for hundreds of dollars, and thi=
s signed Steve Jobs Time Magazine cover is up for $124,995.=C2=A0
Maybe a CyberTruck Hot Wheels signed by Elon Musk himself is more your spee=
d? Good news. It can be yours for only $49,999.99 (or Best Offer).
By contrast, the most expensive Salesforce t-shirt [ https://substack.com/r=
edirect/31a9f623-f9d5-41cb-be59-685452c602c6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7=
GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] on offer is $39.99 and there=E2=80=
=99s practically no market for TikTok company swag despite the product=E2=
=80=99s popularity, adding credence to the idea that Startup Prophecies rel=
ated to companies that become both important and valuable will be worth mor=
e than those related to companies that merely become valuable.=C2=A0
Of course, one way to bet on the success of a younger company like Stripe o=
r Replit or OpenAI would be to find something autographed by Patrick Collis=
on or Amjad Masad or Sam Altman, put it in a protective case, and wait. And=
 given that we=E2=80=99ve focused on the monetary value of the hypothetical=
 NFTs or real collectibles thus far, I wouldn=E2=80=99t blame you for going=
 that route.
But the value of the assets is probably the least interesting piece of the =
Startup Prophecies idea. The greater benefits would come in the form of the=
 impact on the companies, the NFTs=E2=80=99 creators, their holders, and th=
e communities and products that form on top of them.=C2=A0
To understand what those might be, it=E2=80=99s helpful to go into the attr=
ibutes that make NFTs uniquely suited for this purpose. Why NFTs?=C2=A0
Timestamped. Every time an NFT is created or traded, it creates a timestamp=
 associated with the NFT. Timestamps are useful for proving that you predic=
ted something early.=C2=A0A 2023 prediction should be worth more than the s=
ame prediction made in 2025.
Permissionless. Anyone can create a piece related to their favorite company=
 and mint it. Once minted, anyone in the world can buy or sell.=C2=A0Narrat=
ives and worlds can build up without the company=E2=80=99s direct involveme=
nt.
Attributed. It=E2=80=99s easy for the public to verify who each NFT was min=
ted by =E2=80=93 the digital equivalent of a signature =E2=80=93 and who ow=
ns them at any given time.=C2=A0
Composable. The real magic of NFTs is that they=E2=80=99re essentially a fi=
le format that can be plugged into a number of different applications over =
time. Ownership today unlocks access to an evolving ecosystem in the future=
=2E=C2=A0
That last piece =E2=80=93 composability =E2=80=93 is especially important. =
Key to Startup Prophecies is the fact that anyone can build experiences for=
 NFT holders. In the simplest form, that might mean access to a company=E2=
=80=99s community-run Fan Club Discord. The companies themselves may choose=
 to give holders tokengated [ https://substack.com/redirect/5fccebe9-0464-4=
388-87b1-c5345151f6d8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU ] access to events, discounts, or limited edition swag. Peopl=
e can show off their NFTs passively in their wallets or actively in galleri=
es like OnCyber [ https://substack.com/redirect/4aa79b52-014f-4417-ac6f-d27=
360e47071?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ] and build up a richer picture of themselves online. Creators can create=
 derivative works to expand and reinforce the ecosystem, as is happening wi=
th Checks [ https://substack.com/redirect/78a623ce-9879-4361-b9b9-f653993fc=
16b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] an=
d Nouns [ https://substack.com/redirect/f67e9572-7949-4f0b-bf46-da64790346d=
0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. DAO=
s can form to coordinate holders=E2=80=99 activities and provide grants to =
projects that support the company (see this grant-funded Nouns video [ http=
s://substack.com/redirect/346c033e-c37c-45f7-a7cb-418eb5445f7b?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
OXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]). Developers could=
 build apps =E2=80=93 as simple as Startup Prophecy-specific NFT marketplac=
es or as rich as games and virtual worlds =E2=80=93 that incorporate the NF=
Ts. All of this can be done bottoms-up, without any involvement from the co=
mpanies themselves. It=E2=80=99s already happening with digital art.=C2=A0
By creating a new layer, Startup Prophecies adds a whole new dimension to t=
he startup ecosystem and turns supporting companies into a big, open game [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/30d97353-9c01-4368-9230-40ed8c939cfd?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=C2=A0
The fun thing about open, permissionless systems is that they=E2=80=99ll ev=
olve and grow in unpredictable ways. I can=E2=80=99t know all of the differ=
ent ways that people might run with the idea, but there are a few categorie=
s of things I can see happening that have little to do with the price of th=
e NFTs themselves. Here are a few.=C2=A0
Broaden the Community of Supporters
Would Startup Prophecies broaden the community of supporters around the mos=
t ambitious companies? Would artists and videographers and writers find ric=
h new source material in companies aligned with their beliefs? Would compan=
ies themselves create tokengated [ https://substack.com/redirect/5fccebe9-0=
464-4388-87b1-c5345151f6d8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXep=
KbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] experiences for people who hold their NFTs? Would fan =
clubs spring up? Might a DAO of NFT holders even take a board seat one day?=
=C2=A0
Anchor NFTs to =E2=80=9CReal World Assets=E2=80=9D Without Legal Hoops
Would conceptually tying NFTs to real companies create a 3D side-market on =
those companies=E2=80=99 performance? Would company-related NFTs be more va=
luable than a random NFT project by association with something real and imp=
ortant? Could Startup Prophecies be an informal, web3-native bridge between=
 traditional and crypto markets without the legal headaches? Would Startup =
Prophecy NFTs provide a crowdsourced way to assess the value and cultural r=
elevance of companies in between funding rounds?=C2=A0
Showcase Missions You Believe In
Just like art collectors hang their pieces in galleries, Punk owners use th=
eir Punks as PFPs, or angel investors list their best companies in their Tw=
itter bios, might people create wallets and galleries filled with NFTs rela=
ted to companies and missions they believe in? Would the ability to show su=
pport for space exploration or cell therapies expand the universe of people=
 who hold digital assets? Would community members with expertise curate the=
 most exciting companies working in Climate, Biotech, Space, web3, and a nu=
mber of different categories? What would the internet look like if people c=
ould more easily show what they=E2=80=99re for than shout what they=E2=80=
=99re against?=C2=A0
Build a Fantasy Startup Portfolio=C2=A0
Might aspiring VCs use timestamped collections of Startup Prophecies to bui=
ld up a track record? Could a company build a Startup Prophecy Fantasy App =
to rank collectors across a number of metrics and give visibility to people=
 who might not otherwise get noticed by top funds or be able to launch thei=
r own? Would the popularity of certain NFTs even inform VCs=E2=80=99 decisi=
ons about which companies to invest in?=C2=A0
Encourage Optimistic Visions of the Future
If there were a market for Startup Prophecies, would more people use their =
skills =E2=80=93 as artists, writers, videographers, musicians, analysts =
=E2=80=93 to create more optimistic visions of the future? What would the w=
orld look like if the incentives for expressing optimism on the internet ou=
tweighed those for expressing pessimism? Might the market=E2=80=99s desire =
to own assets that represent grand but possible futures push creators towar=
ds definite optimism and sharp analysis instead of pie-in-the-sky guesses?=
=C2=A0
Incentivize Good Quests
If my intuition that NFTs related to companies that become valuable and imp=
ortant will be worth more than companies that simply become valuable, will =
the existence of Startup Prophecies create incentives for more people to Ch=
oose Good Quests [ https://substack.com/redirect/56ef1384-d220-4b0f-ad87-8f=
26da1554e8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRN=
pU ]? Would the knowledge that free marketing and support will exist for th=
e most ambitious companies tackling the biggest challenges tip skilled foun=
ders towards doing something harder than they otherwise might have? Would t=
hat same knowledge give investors more confidence to back those Hard Startu=
ps? Would iterative or copycat ideas fall out of favor?=C2=A0
Accelerate Positive Outcomes
Most importantly, could a positive sum market of Startup Prophecies be self=
-fulfilling? =E2=80=9CDo more people start working together to make somethi=
ng a reality?=E2=80=9D If they do, would it tip the scales enough that a bo=
ld company might succeed where they otherwise might have failed? Would owne=
rship and community involvement provide enough activation energy to turn pe=
ople into advocates?=C2=A0
I framed all of these as open questions because I have no idea how it might=
 play out.=C2=A0
It=E2=80=99s very possible that the vast majority of Startup Prophecy NFTs =
don=E2=80=99t find an audience and fizzle into obscurity. Some might attrac=
t buyers for a while, but fade after the predicted event even if it comes t=
o pass. Interest in projects might wane between funding rounds or big annou=
ncements, creating falsely volatile swings. This being the internet, there =
might very well be a market for negative predictions about companies, and t=
he associated efforts to bring those to life. There=E2=80=99s a good chance=
 that the value of the NFTs never quite connects with the value of the comp=
anies they represent. There=E2=80=99s no way to predict how a complex, dyna=
mic market like this would evolve, or that it would even take off in the fi=
rst place.
But I think there=E2=80=99s something magical here. Instead of trying to sh=
oe-horn everything into becoming a Crypto Thing, it lets the core asset (in=
 this case, a startup, but it could be a movie, or a team, or a game, or wh=
atever) focus on what it does best while a loosely-tethered community of lo=
osely-incentivized supporters forms around it. If nothing else, it=E2=80=99=
s a new form of company merch and memorabilia.=C2=A0
There=E2=80=99s only one way to find out.=C2=A0
I want to experiment with this idea. The easiest way would be to mint deep =
dives I=E2=80=99ve written about companies, and I might do that, but there =
are more native ways to do it. I want to write optimistic short stories abo=
ut the world in which they succeed. I =E2=80=A6 just need to learn how to w=
rite short stories first, so I=E2=80=99m timestamping the idea here in the =
meantime.=C2=A0
If this idea takes off, I want Not Boring Capital=E2=80=99s Portfolio page =
to be an OnCyber gallery full of the NFTs related to the companies we=E2=80=
=99ve invested in.
For now, I=E2=80=99ll start by minting this post on Mirror. If this version=
 of events comes to be, if a rich ecosystem of Startup Prophecies develops,=
 maybe this post will be worth something one day. Who knows. The point here=
 isn=E2=80=99t to make money now =E2=80=93 I=E2=80=99ll donate the proceeds=
