-decoration: underline;">tokengated</a><span> experiences for people who ho=
ld their NFTs? Would fan clubs spring up? Might a DAO of NFT holders even t=
ake a board seat one day?&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Anchor NFTs to =
&#8220;Real World Assets&#8221; Without Legal Hoops</strong></p><p style=3D=
"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">W=
ould conceptually tying NFTs to real companies create a 3D side-market on t=
hose companies&#8217; performance? Would company-related NFTs be more valua=
ble than a random NFT project by association with something real and import=
ant? Could Startup Prophecies be an informal, web3-native bridge between tr=
aditional and crypto markets without the legal headaches? Would Startup Pro=
phecy NFTs provide a crowdsourced way to assess the value and cultural rele=
vance of companies in between funding rounds?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #=
404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Sh=
owcase Missions You Believe In</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Just like art co=
llectors hang their pieces in galleries, Punk owners use their Punks as PFP=
s, or angel investors list their best companies in their Twitter bios, migh=
t people create wallets and galleries filled with NFTs related to companies=
 and missions they believe in? Would the ability to show support for space =
exploration or cell therapies expand the universe of people who hold digita=
l assets? Would community members with expertise curate the most exciting c=
ompanies working in Climate, Biotech, Space, web3, and a number of differen=
t categories? What would the internet look like if people could more easily=
 show what they&#8217;re </span><em>for</em><span> than shout what they&#82=
17;re </span><em>against</em><span>?&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #40=
4040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Buil=
d a Fantasy Startup Portfolio&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #404040;=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Might aspiring VC=
s use timestamped collections of Startup Prophecies to build up a track rec=
ord? Could a company build a Startup Prophecy Fantasy App to rank collector=
s across a number of metrics and give visibility to people who might not ot=
herwise get noticed by top funds or be able to launch their own? Would the =
popularity of certain NFTs even inform VCs&#8217; decisions about which com=
panies to invest in?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Encourage Optimistic Vision=
s of the Future</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If there were a market for Startup Pr=
ophecies, would more people use their skills &#8211; as artists, writers, v=
ideographers, musicians, analysts &#8211; to create more optimistic visions=
 of the future? What would the world look like if the incentives for expres=
sing optimism on the internet outweighed those for expressing pessimism? Mi=
ght the market&#8217;s desire to own assets that represent grand but possib=
le futures push creators towards definite optimism and sharp analysis inste=
ad of pie-in-the-sky guesses?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Incentivize Good Q=
uests</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>If my intuition that NFTs related to comp=
anies that become valuable </span><em>and</em><span> important will be wort=
h more than companies that simply become valuable, will the existence of St=
artup Prophecies create incentives for more people to </span><a href=3D"htt=
ps://substack.com/redirect/56ef1384-d220-4b0f-ad87-8f26da1554e8?j=3DeyJ1Ijo=
iOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel=3D"" style=3D"=
color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;">Choose Good Quests</a><span>? =
Would the knowledge that free marketing and support will exist for the most=
 ambitious companies tackling the biggest challenges tip skilled founders t=
owards doing something harder than they otherwise might have? Would that sa=
me knowledge give investors more confidence to back those Hard Startups? Wo=
uld iterative or copycat ideas fall out of favor?&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><strong>Accelerate Positive Outcomes</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #4040=
40; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Most important=
ly, could a positive sum market of Startup Prophecies be self-fulfilling? &=
#8220;Do more people start working together to make something a reality?&#8=
221; If they do, would it tip the scales enough that a bold company might s=
ucceed where they otherwise might have failed? Would ownership and communit=
y involvement provide enough activation energy to turn people into advocate=
s?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I framed all of these as open questions because I hav=
e no idea how it might play out.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>It&#8217;s very p=
ossible that the vast majority of Startup Prophecy NFTs don&#8217;t find an=
 audience and fizzle into obscurity. Some might attract buyers for a while,=
 but fade after the predicted event even if it comes to pass. Interest in p=
rojects might wane between funding rounds or big announcements, creating fa=
lsely volatile swings. This being the internet, there might very well be a =
market for </span><em>negative</em><span> predictions about companies, and =
the associated efforts to bring those to life. There&#8217;s a good chance =
that the value of the NFTs never quite connects with the value of the compa=
nies they represent. There&#8217;s no way to predict how a complex, dynamic=
 market like this would evolve, or that it would even take off in the first=
 place.</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But I think there&#8217;s something magical her=
e. Instead of trying to shoe-horn everything into becoming a Crypto Thing, =
it lets the core asset (in this case, a startup, but it could be a movie, o=
r a team, or a game, or whatever) focus on what it does best while a loosel=
y-tethered community of loosely-incentivized supporters forms around it. If=
 nothing else, it&#8217;s a new form of company merch and memorabilia.&#160=
;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;">There&#8217;s only one way to find out.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I=
 want to experiment with this idea. The easiest way would be to mint deep d=
ives I&#8217;ve written about companies, and I might do that, but there are=
 more native ways to do it. I want to write optimistic short stories about =
the world in which they succeed. I &#8230; just need to learn how to write =
short stories first, so I&#8217;m timestamping the idea here in the meantim=
e.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If this idea takes off, I want Not Boring Capital&#82=
17;s Portfolio page to be an OnCyber gallery full of the NFTs related to th=
e companies we&#8217;ve invested in.</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-conta=
